See this [Jira ticket](https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-10241) from Spring project for explanation why you don&#39;t see a method doing what you want. The snippet at the above link can be modified like this with an if statement in innermost loop doing the filtering. I assume you have a `Environment env` variable and looking for `String prefix`:

    Map&lt;String, String&gt; properties = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
	if (env instanceof ConfigurableEnvironment) {
		for (PropertySource&lt;?&gt; propertySource : ((ConfigurableEnvironment) env).getPropertySources()) {
			if (propertySource instanceof EnumerablePropertySource) {
				for (String key : ((EnumerablePropertySource) propertySource).getPropertyNames()) {
