You can consider using nested transactions to break the large transaction into smaller, independent ones. This allows for a form of partial rollback, meaning that if an error occurs within one transaction, only that specific transaction will be rolled back, not affecting the changes made in previous batches.
@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW),
